File: .cursor/rules/pipeline-scripts.mdc
Frontmatter:
description: e.g. "Entry points and flags for run_optimized_pipeline.py and optuna_pipeline_search.py; use when editing or running pipeline/scripts."
globs: scripts/**/*.py (or list if you want to include only run_optimized_pipeline.py and optuna_pipeline_search.py).
alwaysApply: false.
Body – fill using:
Main pipeline: python scripts/run_optimized_pipeline.py from repo root. Key defaults: --relation CtD, --embedding_method ComplEx (best run uses RotatE), --embedding_dim 64 (best 128), --results_dir results, --quantum_config_path config/quantum_config.yaml. Full list of flags: see run_optimized_pipeline.py around lines 636–854 (argparse).
Best-run flags (from README): --relation CtD --full_graph_embeddings --embedding_method RotatE --embedding_dim 128 --embedding_epochs 200 --negative_sampling hard --qml_dim 16 --qml_feature_map Pauli --qml_feature_map_reps 2 --qsvc_C 0.1 --optimize_feature_map_reps --run_ensemble --ensemble_method stacking --tune_classical --qml_pre_pca_dim 24 --fast_mode. For local CPU sim add --quantum_config_path config/quantum_config_ideal.yaml (or keep default if your default config is simulator).
Optuna: python scripts/optuna_pipeline_search.py --n_trials <N> --objective <ensemble|qsvc|classical|best>. Optional: --study_name, --results_dir (default results/optuna), --storage. Outputs: results/optuna/optuna_trials.csv, results/optuna/optuna_best.json, SQLite study DB in results/optuna/.
Pipeline outputs: Terminal ends with “RANKING BY TEST PR-AUC” table and “BEST MODELS”. JSON: results/optimized_results_<stamp>.json (contains ranking, config, classical/quantum/ensemble results). Also results/latest_run.csv, results/experiment_history.csv when produced.
